**who —** THE LOUD LATTICE — a LOGISMÓS sphere — a cross-domain message bus

**what —** If the whisper lattice writes inward and quiet, the loud lattice speaks outward and across. A signed message bus between the fourteen domains: any domain can emit a pulse, every crossing is witnessed, every receiver mirrors the signature before it trusts it, and all of it chains to one shared log.

**where —** the inter-domain counterpart to the whisper lattice — a signed cross-domain bus  Framework inputs: the domains; the pulse; the crossing; the mirror; the log  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** If the whisper lattice writes inward and quiet, the loud lattice speaks outward and across. A signed message bus between the fourteen domains: any domain can emit a pulse, every crossing is witnessed, every receiver mirrors the signature before it trusts it, and all of it chains to one shared log.

**how —** Crystallized from LIMEN/pulse, the J-junction, and the whisper tether.

**◌ the mythos —** If the whisper lattice writes inward and quiet, the loud lattice speaks outward and across. A signed message bus between the fourteen domains: any domain can emit a pulse, every crossing is witnessed, every receiver mirrors the signature before it trusts it, and all of it chains to one shared log. a signed pulse, mirrored and accepted across a domain boundary

